  "explanation_html": "<p>Time period (T) $$ = 2\\pi \\sqrt {{l \\over g}} $$</p>\n<p>or $${t \\over n} = 2\\pi \\sqrt {{l \\over g}} $$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$g = {{(4{\\pi ^2})({n^2})l} \\over {{t^2}}}$$</p>\n<p>% error in $$g = {{\\Delta g} \\over g} \\times 100$$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\left( {{{\\Delta l} \\over l} \\times {{2\\Delta l} \\over l}} \\right) \\times 100$$</p>\n<p>$${E_I} = \\left( {{{0.1} \\over {64}} + {{2 \\times 0.1} \\over {128}}} \\right) \\times 100 = 0.3125\\% $$</p>\n<p>$${E_{II}} = \\left( {{{0.1} \\over {64}} + {{2 \\times 0.1} \\over {64}}} \\right) \\times 100 = 0.46875\\% $$</p>\n<p>$${E_{III}} = \\left( {{{0.1} \\over {20}} + {{2 \\times 0.1} \\over {36}}} \\right) \\times 100 = 1.055\\% $$</p>\n<p>Hence, $$\\mathrm{E_I}$$ is minimum.</p>"
